   "info" : "<table width=\"100%\" summary=\"page for UN\"><tr><td>UN</td><td style=\"text-align: right;\">R Documentation</td></tr></table>\n<h2>GDP and Infant Mortality</h2>\n<h3>Description</h3>\n<p>The <code>UN</code> data frame has 207 rows and 2 columns.\nThe data are for 1998 and are from the United Nations; the observations\nare nations of the world.\nThere are some missing data.\n</p>\n<h3>Usage</h3>\n<pre>\nUN\n</pre>\n<h3>Format</h3>\n<p>This data frame contains the following columns:\n</p>\n<dl>\n<dt>infant.mortality</dt><dd>\n<p>Infant morality rate, infant deaths per 1000 live births.\n</p>\n</dd>\n<dt>gdp</dt><dd>\n<p>GDP per capita, in U.S.~dollars.\n</p>\n</dd>\n</dl>\n<h3>Source</h3>\n<p>United Nations (1998) \nSocial indicators.  \nOriginally from <span class=\"samp\">http://www.un.org/Depts/unsd/social/main.htm</span> but no longer there.\n</p>\n<h3>References</h3>\n<p>Fox, J. (2008)\n<em>Applied Regression Analysis and Generalized Linear Models</em>,\nSecond Edition. Sage.  \n</p>\n<p>Fox, J. and Weisberg, S. (2011) \n<em>An R Companion to Applied Regression</em>, Second Edition, Sage.\n</p>\n",
